"Time to first request, peak throughput, and memory (RSS) come from the https://raw.githubusercontent.com/quarkusio/benchmarks/main/images/spring-quarkus-perf-comparison/2026-04-21_09-26-13/metrics-tuned-composite-for-quarkus-light.svg[2026-04-21 perf-lab tuned benchmark] (Quarkus 3.34.3, JDK 25.0.2, GraalVM 25.0.2-graalce, 4 CPUs, `-Xmx512m`).\n"
"Cold-start ranges and container image sizes come from the https://quarkus.io/blog/leyden-2/[Leyden integration benchmarks] and the https://quarkus.io/blog/new-benchmarks/[Mar 2026 performance post].\n"
"For the latest numbers, see the https://github.com/quarkusio/benchmarks#chart-reference[Quarkus benchmarks chart reference]."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: _versions/main/guides/building-native-image.adoc
msgid ""
"For the Leyden AOT cache path, see xref:aot.adoc[the AOT caching guide].\n"
"If native is the right fit for your workload, read on. The next sections walk you through prerequisites, compilation, testing, and container packaging."
msgstr ""

